item.description:
the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higer Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation through NPM registry.
Install: npm install -g codefresh
Install a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: npm install -g codefresh
Update to a specific version: npm install -g codefresh@${VERSION}

the CLI requires node version 8.0.0 or higer Codefresh&rsquo;s CLI is available for installation using YARN.
Install: yarn global add codefresh
Install a specific version: yarn global add codefresh@{VERSION}
Update to latest version: yarn global upgrade codefresh
Update to a specific version: yarn global upgrade codefresh@{VERSION}

You can run the CLI using our official docker image which is published to Dockerhub
Pull the latest version: docker pull codefresh/cli
Pull a specific version: docker pull codefresh/cli:${VERSION}

 Command codefresh annotate image &lt;id&gt;
Annotate an image
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Docker image full name or id    Options    Option Default Description     &ndash;label  annotations to add to the image

 Command codefresh delete environment &lt;id&gt;
Delete an environment
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Environment id

 Command codefresh restart &lt;id&gt;
Restart a build by its id
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Build id    Options    Option Default Description     &ndash;detach  Run build and print workflow ID

 Command codefresh auth use-context &lt;name&gt;
Set the current active authentication context
Positionals    Option Default Description     context-name  a context-name that exists in cfconfig file

 Command codefresh logs &lt;id&gt;
Show logs of a build
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Pipeline id    Options    Option Default Description     &ndash;f  Continue showing build logs until it will finish

 Command codefresh terminate &lt;id&gt;
Terminate a build by its id
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Build id

 Command codefresh patch pipeline &lt;id&gt;
Apply changes to a pipeline
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  pipeline id   repo-owner  repository owner   repo-name  repository name    Options    Option Default Description     &ndash;context  context in form of: type=name   &ndash;engine-cluster  K8 cluster name to use for execution   &ndash;engine-namespace  K8 namespace in the chosen cluster to use for execution   &ndash;default-engine  Use the default engine configured by the system

 Command codefresh wait &lt;id..&gt;
Wait until a condition will be met on a build
Positionals    Option Default Description     id  Build id    Options    Option Default Description     &ndash;status  Build status   &ndash;debug  Show debug output until the condition will be met   &ndash;timeout 30 Define a timeout for the wait operation in minutes
